Implemented Vercel Speed Insights for Next.js

Summary:
Successfully installed and configured @vercel/speed-insights package for the Next.js 16.1.6 App Router project.

Changes Made:

1. Installed Package:
   - Added @vercel/speed-insights@^1.3.1 to dependencies using pnpm
   - Updated package.json with the new dependency
   - Generated pnpm-lock.yaml with all dependency resolutions

2. Modified Files:
   - client/src/app/layout.tsx:
     * Added import for SpeedInsights component from '@vercel/speed-insights/next'
     * Placed <SpeedInsights /> component inside the <body> tag after the Providers section
     * The component will automatically track page navigation and performance metrics

Implementation Details:
- Used the Next.js 13.5+ App Router approach as this project uses Next.js 16.1.6
- Imported from '@vercel/speed-insights/next' (not the react version) for automatic route tracking
- Positioned the component at the end of the body tag to avoid blocking page rendering
- No configuration needed - the component works out of the box with zero-config setup

Verification:
✓ Build completed successfully with no errors
✓ Linter passed with no issues
✓ TypeScript compilation successful
✓ All 16 routes generated correctly

The Speed Insights component is now active and will collect performance metrics when deployed to Vercel. The component automatically tracks:
- Core Web Vitals (LCP, FID, CLS, etc.)
- Page load times
- Navigation performance
- Real User Monitoring (RUM) data
